prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "The system must store an application in a pending state while it is being reviewed.",
      "evidence_quote": "'When someone submits an application, it remains pending while it is being reviewed.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "After review, the system must update the application status to either approved or rejected.",
      "evidence_quote": "'After review, the application is either approved or rejected.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Once a decision is made, the system must finalize the application process.",
      "evidence_quote": "'Once a decision is made, the process continues toward completion.'"
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The system must mark every application as finalized upon completion of the process.",
      "evidence_quote": "'In both cases, whether approved or rejected, the application is finalized at the end, marking the completion of the process.'"
    }
  ]
}

llm_response:
```json
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "The system must store an application in a pending state while it is being reviewed.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall store an application in a pending state during review."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "After review, the system must update the application status to either approved or rejected.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall update the application status to either approved or rejected after review."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Once a decision is made, the system must finalize the application process.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall finalize the application process once a decision is made."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "The system must mark every application as finalized upon completion of the process.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall mark every application as finalized upon process completion."
    }
  ]
}
```
